        <id>/blog/predicting-airway-complications/</id>
        
        <content type="html" xml:base="/blog/predicting-airway-complications/">&lt;p&gt;The baseline risk for difficult airway (8-11%) and severe complications (38%) is high in all critically ill patients. Difficult airway greatly increases the risk of severe complcations during intubation (30-35% vs 50-60%). Scoring systems for elective surgery therefore seriously underestimate risk in this cohort.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Consider the &lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;doi.org&#x2F;10.1164&#x2F;rccm.201210-1851OC&quot;&gt;MACOCHA Score&lt;&#x2F;a&gt; to identify patients at paritcularly high risk and plan accordingly.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a rel=&quot;external&quot; href=&quot;https:&#x2F;&#x2F;www.mdcalc.com&#x2F;calc&#x2F;10476&#x2F;macocha-score&quot;&gt;MACOCHA score on MDCalc&lt;&#x2F;a&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is worth noting that Mallampati score does the heavy lifting in prediction difficult intubations (Identified 51&#x2F;82 alone, compared to 62&#x2F;82 with the full score).&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;score&quot;&gt;Score&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;table&gt;&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Factor&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Score&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;&lt;&#x2F;thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;Patient factors&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Mallampati III or IV&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;5&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Obstructive Sleep Apnoea&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;2&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Restricted neck movement&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Mouth opening &amp;lt;3cm&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;Pathology factors&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Coma&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Severe hypoxaemia &amp;lt;80%&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;Operator factors&lt;&#x2F;em&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td&gt;Non-anaesthetist&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;td&gt;1&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;tbody&gt;&lt;&#x2F;table&gt;
